Pwrake, Parallel Workflow extension for Rake  Masahiro Tanaka 2010-06-10

* Required package

  Ruby 1.8.x + Rake 0.8.7
  or Ruby 1.9.x

* Included packages

  METIS 5.0pre2 (for graph partition)
    http://glaros.dtc.umn.edu/gkhome/fetch/sw/metis/metis-5.0pre2.tar.gz
  Montage ('mImgHdr.c' is added)
    http://montage.ipac.caltech.edu/download/Montage_v3.2_beta4.tar.gz

* Preparation

    tar xvzf pwrake-0pre1.tgz
    cd pwrake-0pre1/pkg/metis-5.0pre2
    make all
    cd ../Montage_v3.2_beta4
    make
    ( optionally, copy binaries to your PATH )

* Montage workflow Demo

  1. Single host

    ( do "Preparation" above )
    cd pwrake-0pre1/demo
    ./pwrake -f affinity.rake LOG=`date +%Y%m%d%H%M%S`

  2. Multi-hosts with NFS

    cd nfs_dir
    ( do "Preparation" above )
    cd pwrake-0pre1/demo
    ./pwrake -f affinity.rake NODE=tsukuba4 LOG=`date +%Y%m%d%H%M%S`

  3. Multi-hosts with Gfarm

    mkdir /tmp/$USER
    gfarm2fs /tmp/$USER
    cd /tmp/$USER/$HOME/somewhere
    ( do "Preparation" above )
    cd pwrake-0pre1/demo
    ./pwrake -f affinity.rake FS=gfarm NODE=tsukuba4 LOG=`date +%Y%m%d%H%M%S`
